io.amelia.support

Class VoluntaryWithCause<Type,Cause extends java.lang.Exception>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.amelia.support.Voluntary<Type>
      • io.amelia.support.VoluntaryWithCause<Type,Cause>

  • public final class VoluntaryWithCause<Type,Cause extends java.lang.Exception>
extends Voluntary<Type>
    An expanded container object which may or may not contain a non-null value and/or exception, is similar to Optional but adds error handling. If a value is present, isPresent() will return true and get() will return the value. If a cause is present, hasErrored() will return true and getException() will return the cause.

    Additional methods that depend on the presence or absence of a contained value are provided, such as orElse() (return a default value if value not present) and ifPresent() (execute a block of code if the value is present).

    Additional methods for interfacing with Java 8 features are also present, such as Voluntary.of(Optional). Methods ending with "compatible" are intended in mimic the logic of similar methods found in Optional, e.g., flatMapCompatible(Function)

    See Also:
    Optional

        If a value is present, apply the provided VoluntaryWithCause-bearing mapping function to it, return that result, otherwise return an empty VoluntaryWithCause. This method is similar to map(Function), but the provided mapper is one whose result is already an VoluntaryWithCause, and if invoked, flatMap does not wrap it with an additional VoluntaryWithCause.
